   (
     'interview-techniques',
     'What are effective interview techniques for enumerators?',
-    '<p><strong>Effective Interview Techniques</strong> are crucial for collecting high-quality data.</p><h3>Best practices:</h3><ul><li><strong>Build rapport</strong> with respondents</li><li><strong>Ask questions exactly as written</strong></li><li><strong>Use neutral probing</strong> for incomplete answers</li><li><strong>Maintain confidentiality</strong></li><li><strong>Be patient and respectful</strong></li><li><strong>Record answers accurately</strong></li></ul><p>Good interview techniques help ensure data quality and improve response rates by creating a positive experience for respondents.</p>',
